{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Mandatory Custodial Sentence for Sexual Violence with a Weapon at any Age",
        "additional_details": "Sexual violence is recognised by the UK Government as a weapon of war and one of the most serious violations of human rights. We believe the use of a weapon in a sexual offence demonstrates premeditation, extreme threat to life, and lasting trauma for victims.\r\n\r\nYet sentencing guidelines allow significant judicial discretion, and age can be used as a mitigating factor even in cases involving weapons so the offender avoids prison. We believe this undermines public confidence and fails survivors.\r\n",
        "background": "Introduce a statutory minimum custodial sentence for any sexual offence under the Sexual Offences Act 2003 where the offender used, threatened, or carried a weapon. Remove age as a bar to custody in these cases.",
